      "writtenOn": "2026-04-13T12:45:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The check is needed because `s` here is the body after `ParseQuotes` strips the opening delimiter, newline, and whitespace prefix. `ParseQuotes` finds the closing delimiter from the end, so the body can start with `\"\"\"`. For example:\n\n```\n\"\"\"\n\t\"\"\"0\n\t\"\"\"\n```\n\n`ParseQuotes` strips `\"\"\"\\n\\t`, leaving `s` \u003d `\"\"\"0\\n\\t\"\"\"`. Without the check, `Unquote` would accept this as body `\"\"\"0`, but the scanner would greedily match `\\t\"\"\"` as the closer — so we need to reject it here to stay consistent.\n\nIn other words, one of the added test cases fails without this check.",
      "parentUuid": "b8fb7f51_dc7bb068",
      "revId": "cedf9da073d4d11d9a62a16b5c3513771afce265",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
